    var neighbourhoods_for_map = {"1":{"neighbourhood_id":"1","account_id":"160013","label":"Sarasota","icon":"\/neighbourhood.png","splash_image":"county-1200.jpg","description":"Fall in love with colorful bungalow shops lining Fruitville Road near downtown Sarasota, stroll through historic districts, such as Burns Court, Laurel Park and Towles Court Artist Colony, and visit extravagant area gardens and museums. \r\n\r\nFashionable, yet unassuming, the city of Sarasota might surprise visitors with an unexpected melange of art galleries, antique collections, niche retail shops, local restaurants, bistros, and nightlife venues.\r\n\r\nThere's enough here to entertain visits of any length - Just ask our seasonal snowbirds!","zoom_level":"13","lat":"27.33727710","lng":"-82.54082650","directory":"userFiles\/a\/1\/6\/0\/0\/1\/3"},"3":{"neighbourhood_id":"3","account_id":"160013","label":"Lido Key-St Armands","icon":"\/neighbourhood.png","splash_image":"lido-starmands.jpg","description":"For those seeking eco-adventure, beaches, shopping and dining without the need of a car, look no further than Lido Key. This island is just a short drive over the awe-inspiring Ringling Causeway.\r\n\r\nWithout a doubt, you'll first want to stop and stroll around St. Armands Circle - one of Sarasota County's finest boutique shopping and dining destinations. Afterward, enjoy a siesta on Lido Beach or, if it's evening, watch a gorgeous setting sun disappear in the Gulf of Mexico.\r\n\r\nFinally, lest we forget, stop by Mote Aquarium and Ken Thompson Park for some family friendly activities.","zoom_level":"13","lat":"27.31846350","lng":"-82.57808570","directory":"userFiles\/a\/1\/6\/0\/0\/1\/3"},"2":{"neighbourhood_id":"2","account_id":"160013","label":"Siesta Key","icon":"\/neighbourhood.png","splash_image":"SIESTAKEY-1.jpg","description":"Siesta Key's legacy continues to grow. Siesta Beach, named America's #1 beach in the country in 2011, is regularly recognized as one of the world's best island vacation destinations. The sand on Siesta Beach, made of finely crushed pure quartz, is always soft and cool to the touch.\r\n\r\nSurrounded by vacation rentals and nearby beach access, Siesta Key Village offers relaxed dining with live music, souvenir and beach apparel shopping, and popular club venues and bars.\r\n\r\nHome to beach sports and sand sculpting competitions, there is never a dull moment on this fun filled key.","zoom_level":"13","lat":"27.27614920","lng":"-82.56429220","directory":"userFiles\/a\/1\/6\/0\/0\/1\/3"},"9":{"neighbourhood_id":"9","account_id":"160013","label":"Lakewood Ranch","icon":"\/neighbourhood.png","splash_image":"MosaicOpt_LakewoodRanch.jpg","description":"Spend the afternoon strolling through Lakewood Ranch's Main Street \u2014 a hub of boutique shopping, outdoor dining and even a miniature golf course.","zoom_level":"13","lat":"27.39416930","lng":"-82.43532330","directory":"userFiles\/a\/1\/6\/0\/0\/1\/3"},"13":{"neighbourhood_id":"13","account_id":"160013","label":"University Corridor","icon":"\/neighbourhood.png","splash_image":"MosaicOpt_Ringling_Book-293.jpg","description":"Explore one of the Gulf Coast of Florida's rising shopping hot spots. With the newest addition, the Mall at University Town Center, this area literally has stores ( & dining establishments) for miles, ranging from boutique and luxury to bargain deals.","zoom_level":"13","lat":"27.38482820","lng":"-82.55870270","directory":"userFiles\/a\/1\/6\/0\/0\/1\/3"},"6":{"neighbourhood_id":"6","account_id":"160013","label":"Venice","icon":"\/neighbourhood.png","splash_image":"MosaicOpt_Venice_Beach___Sharkey_s_SP8QX6r0Le","description":"Downtown Venice is lush with boutique shops, delicious eateries and cafes, and pristine parks. Though long touted as a great place to retire, Venice has more than enough spunk to make for a great family getaway!  With kid and dog friendly restaurants, smooth bike trails, beaches, and a rich circus heritage, you'll be booking your next stay before you leave.\r\n\r\nVenice is a city of treasures - one of which is Capersen Beach. The beach was recently selected as a \"best beach to visit before summer ends\" by MSN Living. The publication pointed to the town's idyllic, laid back, bike friendly seaside location. And another treasure to many in Brohard Park - one of the only pet friendly beaches in Sarasota County.","zoom_level":"13","lat":"27.10157600","lng":"-82.45440400","directory":"userFiles\/a\/1\/6\/0\/0\/1\/3"},"10":{"neighbourhood_id":"10","account_id":"160013","label":"Longboat Key","icon":"\/neighbourhood.png","splash_image":"lido-1200.jpg","description":"The beaches on Longboat Key are some of the best to escape the crowd. While maintaining the feeling of a quiet escape, Longboat Key is only a short drive from the energizing bustle of St. Armands Circle and downtown Sarasota. This island is home to resports offering five-star dining, spa services and championship golf courses.\r\n\r\nWhether or not you decide to stay at a Longboat Key resort, dining options on the island feature some of the best cuisine in the area. Dine at Euphemia Hay, Dry Dock Waterfront Gri","zoom_level":"13","lat":"27.40823100","lng":"-82.65608900","directory":"userFiles\/a\/1\/6\/0\/0\/1\/3"},"8":{"neighbourhood_id":"8","account_id":"160013","label":"Englewood-Northport","icon":"\/neighbourhood.png","splash_image":"Englewood-northport.jpg","description":"Englewood is painted - quite literally - by artists. Street murals adorn the walls of Englewood's darling West Dearborn Street, a strip of local shops and outdoor dining establishments. Nearby is Lemon Bay Park, a 210 acre nature based park with more than a mile and a half of shorline on the Lemon bay Aquatic Preserve.\r\n\r\nEnglewood is a naturalist's paradise where songbirds chirp and splendid sunsets are witnessed over Manasota Key. No wonder so many artists live and work there - inspiration is abundant in in the area's natural beauty.\r\n\r\nNorth Port is freckled with nature trails, canals and natural springs. In 2013 North Port was recognized as a Playful City USA for the fourth consecutive year.  The city is home to 26 parks, 80 miles of freshwater canals, and 800 miles of local roadways perfect for biking. \r\n\r\nPerhaps one surprising fact - the city of North Port is home to one of the most challenging mountain bike trails in Southwest Florida. One trail, along the Myakkahatchee Creek, cuts through the heart of North Port, and is lined with exotic moss covered oaks, slash pines and thick palmettos.","zoom_level":"13","lat":"26.96270500","lng":"-82.35882400","directory":"userFiles\/a\/1\/6\/0\/0\/1\/3"},"7":{"neighbourhood_id":"7","account_id":"160013","label":"Manasota Key","icon":"\/neighbourhood.png","splash_image":"MosaicOpt_ManasotaKey_iStock_000026378849Medi","description":"Manasota Key is an 11 mile long peninsula transformed into a barrier island. Stump Pass Beach State Park is a popular stop on the island, featuring a mile of beach where seashells and shark's teeth wash ashore. Nearby, Englewood Beach features a boardwalk, restaurants, and tourist shops. On the northern side of the Key, Blind Pass Beach is an excellent place to search for shark's teeth and, further north, Manasota Beach offers a popular snorkeling area.","zoom_level":"13","lat":"26.93678300","lng":"-82.36849300","directory":"userFiles\/a\/1\/6\/0\/0\/1\/3"},"5":{"neighbourhood_id":"5","account_id":"160013","label":"Casey Key-Osprey-Nokomis","icon":"\/neighbourhood.png","splash_image":"MosaicOpt_Casey_Key___Umbrella_Sl648WnWXkkQeR","description":"Casey Key is a narrow island near Nokomis. Isolated and exclusive, Casey Key is the ultimate getaway retreat and the seasonal home of celebrities such as Steven King and Rosie O'Donnell.  One popular stop is certainly the Casey Key Fish House. Old Florida at its best, this stop is right on the water and features exotic cocktails and a waterside tiki bar.\r\n\r\nCasey Key and Nokomis are known as great fishing locations, in particular Blackburn Point Road - conveniently located right next to the Fish House - and the southern end of Nokomis Beach, which leads right up to the north Venice Jetty.","zoom_level":"13","lat":"27.17595700","lng":"-82.49469900","directory":"userFiles\/a\/1\/6\/0\/0\/1\/3"},"12":{"neighbourhood_id":"12","account_id":"160013","label":"I75 Corridor","icon":"\/neighbourhood.png","splash_image":"gulfgate.jpg","description":"Nearby Clark Road and Interstate 75, find Twin Lakes Park - a training base for both minor and major league baseball and grounds to festivals and parties, as well as major shopping stores, popular sports bars and other dining options.","zoom_level":"13","lat":"27.26968300","lng":"-82.49915200","directory":"userFiles\/a\/1\/6\/0\/0\/1\/3"}};
